  <wpt lat="37.976276027038693" lon="38.737300029024482">
    <ele>2012.5</ele>
    <time>2014-04-11T16:04:13Z</time>
    <name>04 BC Nemrut Daggi</name>
    <cmt>Nemrut Daggi is meanwhile a World culture heritage. After a very steep car climb we got into the Nemrut park and were positively surprised that we are allowed to stay for the night within the park. The Nemrut is exceptional at sunrise and sunset. It was still (in April) freezing during the night given the altitude of 2.100 meter. Busses come in the morning with tourist to experience the sunrise. 
</cmt>
    <desc>Nemrut Daggi is meanwhile a World culture heritage. After a very steep car climb we got into the Nemrut park and were positively surprised that we are allowed to stay for the night within the park. The Nemrut is exceptional at sunrise and sunset. It was still (in April) freezing during the night given the altitude of 2.100 meter. Busses come in the morning with tourist to experience the sunrise. 
</desc>
    <sym>Campground</sym>
    <type>user</type>
    <extensions>
      <gpxx:WaypointExtension>
        <gpxx:DisplayMode>SymbolAndName</gpxx:DisplayMode>
      </gpxx:WaypointExtension>
      <wptx1:WaypointExtension>
        <wptx1:DisplayMode>SymbolAndName</wptx1:DisplayMode>
