        <ctx:CreationTime>2014-05-18T10:31:28Z</ctx:CreationTime>
      </ctx:CreationTimeExtension>
    </extensions>
  </wpt>

  <wpt lat="42.489631148055196" lon="78.391377925872803">
    <ele>0.02</ele>
    <time>1970-01-01T00:00:00Z</time>
    <name>33 BC guesthouse Karakol</name>
    <cmt>We met in town a Belgium tour organizer who recommended this guesthouse as a good cost effective place to stay. We could park the car in the patio behind the closed fence and protected from wind. Hot clean showers are available in the sauna area. Breakfast was really great! They don’t serve dinner but a good price/value restaurant owned by a Muslim (no beer) is just around the corner. We can really recommend this place to budget travelers.
Price: 200 Sum (2,60€) /person/night (use of hot shower inlcuded), 200 Sum (2,60 €) /person for breakfast, 350 Sum (4,55€)/person for a good dinner 
Campground: after fense/wall, we did sleep in our car, up to 5-6 cars can park next to the guesthouse
Sanitair: European style toilet, hot shower (old but clean) 
Laundery service: 300 Sumoni (3,90€/machine)
Electricity: we didn't use
Wifi: yes (free)



</cmt>
    <desc>We met in town a Belgium tour organizer who recommended this guesthouse as a good cost effective place to stay. We could park the car in the patio behind the closed fence and protected from wind. Hot clean showers are available in the sauna area. Breakfast was really great! They don’t serve dinner but a good price/value restaurant owned by a Muslim (no beer) is just around the corner. We can really recommend this place to budget travelers.
