  <wpt lat="47.91151667945087" lon="106.98115001432598">
    <ele>0.02</ele>
    <time>1970-01-01T00:00:00Z</time>
    <name>51 Oasis Camping &amp; guesthouse</name>
    <cmt>The “Oasis” is the ultimate meeting place for overland travelers in Ulaan Baatar. The traveling public is very mixed. Motorcyclists predominate while we were there. Motorists as we are rather in the minority. The little parking in the back garden has space for maybe 6-7 LandCruiser type cars. Then you stand car to car and it gets challenging to open the doors. However also a biger Unimog can fit. 

The Restaurant is open from till 18:30 and has a good European cuisine; Wiener Schnitzel (!) is on the menu. The Wifi is free and useful. You can relax and work on your laptop the whole day in the restaurant or on the terrace. Also laundry service is available. A disadvantage however is the sanitary facilities that consist of only 1 toilet per gender in each of which a tiny sink are attached. Toilet cleanness can become a big challenge when the guestrooms and gers are fully occupied. There are 8 hot water showers, which are included in the price, if they are not occupied by locals.

We had great weather in UB. However, we heard from other overlanders that Oasis has a real challenge when raining as the garden/parking gets fully flood. 

The cuisine is full day and night self serve for drinks. You take out of the fridge what you want and put it on your personal card. You pay when you leave. 

The kittchen closes at 18:30. We could not order any more when we arrived at 18:50. The next day a motorbike group arrived and could even order until 21:15.</cmt>
    <desc>The “Oasis” is the ultimate meeting place for overland travelers in Ulaan Baatar. The traveling public is very mixed. Motorcyclists predominate while we were there. Motorists as we are rather in the minority. The little parking in the back garden has space for maybe 6-7 LandCruiser type cars. Then you stand car to car and it gets challenging to open the doors. However also a biger Unimog can fit. 

The Restaurant is open from till 18:30 and has a good European cuisine; Wiener Schnitzel (!) is on the menu. The Wifi is free and useful. You can relax and work on your laptop the whole day in the restaurant or on the terrace. Also laundry service is available. A disadvantage however is the sanitary facilities that consist of only 1 toilet per gender in each of which a tiny sink are attached. Toilet cleanness can become a big challenge when the guestrooms and gers are fully occupied. There are 8 hot water showers, which are included in the price, if they are not occupied by locals.

We had great weather in UB. However, we heard from other overlanders that Oasis has a real challenge when raining as the garden/parking gets fully flood. 

The cuisine is full day and night self serve for drinks. You take out of the fridge what you want and put it on your personal card. You pay when you leave. 

The kittchen closes at 18:30. We could not order any more when we arrived at 18:50. The next day a motorbike group arrived and could even order until 21:15.</desc>
    <sym>Campground</sym>
    <type>user</type>
    <extensions>
      <gpxx:WaypointExtension>
        <gpxx:DisplayMode>SymbolAndName</gpxx:DisplayMode>
      </gpxx:WaypointExtension>
      <wptx1:WaypointExtension>
        <wptx1:DisplayMode>SymbolAndName</wptx1:DisplayMode>
      </wptx1:WaypointExtension>
      <ctx:CreationTimeExtension>
        <ctx:CreationTime>1970-01-01T00:00:00Z</ctx:CreationTime>
      </ctx:CreationTimeExtension>
    </extensions>
  </wpt>

